A common ingest schema (OTel GenAI semconv) lets one observability plane accept spans from every SDK.

```typescript
type OTelSpan = {
  'gen_ai.system': string; 'gen_ai.request.model': string;
  'gen_ai.usage.input_tokens': number; 'gen_ai.usage.output_tokens': number;
};

function normalize(raw: any, sdk: string): OTelSpan {
  if (sdk === 'openai') return {
    'gen_ai.system': 'openai', 'gen_ai.request.model': raw.model,
    'gen_ai.usage.input_tokens': raw.usage.prompt_tokens,
    'gen_ai.usage.output_tokens': raw.usage.completion_tokens };
  // langchain shape differs -> mapped to the SAME schema
  return {
    'gen_ai.system': 'langchain', 'gen_ai.request.model': raw.llm_model,
    'gen_ai.usage.input_tokens': raw.token_usage.input,
    'gen_ai.usage.output_tokens': raw.token_usage.output };
}

console.log(normalize({ model: 'gpt-4', usage: { prompt_tokens: 100, completion_tokens: 50 } }, 'openai'));
console.log(normalize({ llm_model: 'claude', token_usage: { input: 120, output: 40 } }, 'langchain'));
```

Output:

```
{ 'gen_ai.system': 'openai', 'gen_ai.request.model': 'gpt-4', 'gen_ai.usage.input_tokens': 100, 'gen_ai.usage.output_tokens': 50 }
{ 'gen_ai.system': 'langchain', 'gen_ai.request.model': 'claude', 'gen_ai.usage.input_tokens': 120, 'gen_ai.usage.output_tokens': 40 }
```

**Why a common schema is the enabler.** Without it, every SDK (OpenAI, Anthropic, LangChain, LlamaIndex, vLLM) has its own span shape, and you would build N ingest pipelines. The OTel GenAI semantic conventions give *one* schema — normalize each SDK's native events to it once, and the rest of the dashboard (cost, traces, evals) is SDK-agnostic. This is why Langfuse, Phoenix, and OpenLLMetry converged on OTel: instrument once, ship compatible spans from anywhere. The capstone ingests from at least four SDK families through this single schema. The next exercises cost-attribute and catch regressions.
